 Dhaka, June 7 (bdnews24.com)-- BNP has called for a strong governance of the open market system. The main opposition also advocated that private ownership, cooperative ownership and state ownership as complementary to each other. BNP chief Khaleda Zia deliberated upon BNP's preference for overall economic policies of the government in her first-ever shadow budget proposal on Monday ahead of the June 10 national budget by finance minister AMA Muhith. Also leader of the opposition, Khaleda said in her budget proposal that without strong entrepreneurship it would not be possible to survive in today's competitive world. She urged for lessening the radical disparity between the poor and rich and emancipation of the toiling masses. To that end, the main opposition called for strong government measures specially targeted towards the poor and employment-generation schemes. Khaleda laid out three objectives of the budget saying that budget should be for the people, for development and for increasing development. She said that the government should prioritise power, education, health and infrastructure. b
